  title: `Kantianism, Utopias, and Dystopias`,
  subtitle: `Treating people as ends — when design does it, and when it quietly refuses.`,
  summary: `Kant's categorical imperative read through science fiction's utopias and dystopias: what a world that took persons-as-ends seriously would actually look like.`,
  learningGoals: [`Apply the categorical imperative to product, policy, and platform design decisions.`, `Distinguish genuine respect for persons from its bureaucratic simulation.`, `Read utopias and dystopias as arguments about what technology protects or corrodes.`],
